# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv and micro-envs within a project.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a pyproject.toml, the lock file can be omitted.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock can be included or excluded, see:
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock can be included or excluded, see:
#   https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/usage/project/#commit-the-lock-file
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

